{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377127372,"sessionID":"ses_1f07e2ebdffeInlu2gX9ePTiIa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_X2kqYWTZhiwhog8EQf1Nhujk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+## GO:1990334 label and definition update\n+\n+Relevant design pattern checked: `src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml`.\n+\n+This term is an existing cellular component term for a protein complex with GAP activity. The available pattern models protein complexes by a molecular function using `capable_of` and an equivalent class axiom. I did not add a logical definition because this edit only updates the label, definition, and synonyms for species-neutral wording, and the current term is already classified under `GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex`.\n+\n+Existing ontology precedent checked:\n+\n+- `GO:0160065 ! SIN/MEN signaling complex` uses the combined SIN/MEN wording for a species-neutral cellular component label.\n+- `GO:0034973 ! Sid2-Mob1 complex` keeps organism-specific complex names as synonyms where appropriate.\n+\n+Decision: keep the existing parentage and `part_of spindle pole body` relation unchanged, rename the term to the species-neutral label requested in the issue, and add the previous species-specific names as narrow synonyms.\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+## PMID:16449187 \"Disappearance of the budding yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex from the mother-bound spindle pole contributes to mitotic exit.\"\n+\n+Validated PMID:16449187 with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:16449187`. The record title, authors, journal, DOI, and full-text content match the existing GO definition provenance.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"Budding yeast spindle position checkpoint is engaged by misoriented spindles and prevents mitotic exit by inhibiting the G protein Tem1 through the GTPase-activating protein (GAP) Bub2/Bfa1.\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"The Bub2/Bfa1 GTPase-activating protein (GAP) plays a key role in this process by keeping Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"The Bub2–Bfa1 complex is proposed to prevent mitotic exit by stimulating Tem1 GTPase activity both in budding and in fission yeast\"\n+\n+Decision: retain PMID:16449187 as definition provenance. The issue requests species-neutral wording; the paper directly supports the existing budding yeast example and states that Bub2-Bfa1-like regulation is relevant to fission yeast as well.\n*** Update File: terms/GO_1990334.obo\n@@\n-name: Bfa1-Bub2 complex\n+name: SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex\n namespace: cellular_component\n-def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Tem1 GTPase, thus regulating a signal transduction cascade, called the mitotic exit network (MEN), which is required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. Bub2/Bfa1 keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for a Ras-family GTPase in the septation initiation network (SIN) or mitotic exit network (MEN), thereby regulating signal transduction cascades required for cytokinesis and mitotic exit.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+synonym: \"Bfa1-Bub2 complex\" NARROW []\n+synonym: \"Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex\" NARROW []\n is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md\nM terms/GO_1990334.obo","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+## GO:1990334 label and definition update\n+\n+Relevant design pattern checked: `src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml`.\n+\n+This term is an existing cellular component term for a protein complex with GAP activity. The available pattern models protein complexes by a molecular function using `capable_of` and an equivalent class axiom. I did not add a logical definition because this edit only updates the label, definition, and synonyms for species-neutral wording, and the current term is already classified under `GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex`.\n+\n+Existing ontology precedent checked:\n+\n+- `GO:0160065 ! SIN/MEN signaling complex` uses the combined SIN/MEN wording for a species-neutral cellular component label.\n+- `GO:0034973 ! Sid2-Mob1 complex` keeps organism-specific complex names as synonyms where appropriate.\n+\n+Decision: keep the existing parentage and `part_of spindle pole body` relation unchanged, rename the term to the species-neutral label requested in the issue, and add the previous species-specific names as narrow synonyms.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@\n+## PMID:16449187 \"Disappearance of the budding yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex from the mother-bound spindle pole contributes to mitotic exit.\"\n+\n+Validated PMID:16449187 with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:16449187`. The record title, authors, journal, DOI, and full-text content match the existing GO definition provenance.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"Budding yeast spindle position checkpoint is engaged by misoriented spindles and prevents mitotic exit by inhibiting the G protein Tem1 through the GTPase-activating protein (GAP) Bub2/Bfa1.\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"The Bub2/Bfa1 GTPase-activating protein (GAP) plays a key role in this process by keeping Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation\"\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"The Bub2–Bfa1 complex is proposed to prevent mitotic exit by stimulating Tem1 GTPase activity both in budding and in fission yeast\"\n+\n+Decision: retain PMID:16449187 as definition provenance. The issue requests species-neutral wording; the paper directly supports the existing budding yeast example and states that Bub2-Bfa1-like regulation is relevant to fission yeast as well.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n@@ -1,10 +1,11 @@\n [Term]\n id: GO:1990334\n-name: Bfa1-Bub2 complex\n+name: SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex\n namespace: cellular_component\n-def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Tem1 GTPase, thus regulating a signal transduction cascade, called the mitotic exit network (MEN), which is required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. Bub2/Bfa1 keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for a Ras-family GTPase in the septation initiation network (SIN) or mitotic exit network (MEN), thereby regulating signal transduction cascades required for cytokinesis and mitotic exit.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+synonym: \"Bfa1-Bub2 complex\" NARROW []\n+synonym: \"Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex\" NARROW []\n is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex\n relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body\n created_by: bhm\n creation_date: 2014-03-17T14:34:21Z\n-\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/